{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:28:36.065767+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: f50a83e0af3fef00acef8684b35380ce80199414)", "id": "lc_4eec9f25-e94e-45df-8006-995fc35efb83"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"package\": {\n    \"homepage\": \".\",\n    \"dependencies\": {\n      \"@emotion/react\": \"^11.10.5\",\n      \"@emotion/styled\": \"^11.10.5\",\n      \"@mui/icons-material\": \"^5.11.0\",\n      \"@mui/material\": \"^5.11.5\",\n      \"@testing-library/jest-dom\": \"^5.16.5\",\n      \"@testing-library/react\": \"^13.4.0\",\n      \"@testing-library/user-event\": \"^13.5.0\",\n      \"firebase\": \"^9.16.0\",\n      \"react\": \"^18.2.0\",\n      \"react-dom\": \"^18.2.0\",\n      \"react-router-dom\": \"^6.7.0\",\n      \"react-scripts\": \"5.0.1\",\n      \"web-vitals\": \"^2.1.4\"\n    },\n    \"scripts\": {\n      \"serve\": \"serve -s build\",\n      \"build-and-serve\": \"npm run build && npm run serve\",\n      \"start\": \"react-scripts start\",\n      \"build\": \"react-scripts build\",\n      \"test\": \"react-scripts test\",\n      \"eject\": \"react-scripts eject\",\n      \"predeploy\": \"npm run build\",\n      \"deploy\": \"gh-pages -d build\",\n      \"pull\": \"git pull && npm i && npm start\"\n    },\n    \"devDependencies\": {\n      \"gh-pages\": \"^3.2.3\"\n    },\n    \"eslintConfig\": {\n      \"extends\": [\"react-app\", \"react-app/jest\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n", "id": "lc_2a42bb81-1cf8-45e9-833d-dc14a267ed86"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "a2f97894-ef57-41d2-8aff-d7978daeb5af", "tool_call_id": "call_01_UdQHxiQG5E7id85jpr8f3912", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:28:53.992984+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I now have a complete picture of the repository's npm scripts and guidance. Here is the summary.\n\n---\n\n## npm Scripts Related to Local Development & Deployment\n\n### 1. Scripts in `package.json` (template authoring / repo maintenance)\n\n| Script | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `start` | Runs `react-scripts start` – launches the **local dev server** |\n| `build` | Runs `react-scripts build` – creates an **optimised production build** in `build/` |\n| `test` | Runs `react-scripts test` – executes the test suite |\n| `eject` | Runs `react-scripts eject` – ejects from CRA (irreversible) |\n| `predeploy` | Runs `npm run build` automatically **before** `deploy` |\n| `deploy` | Runs `gh-pages -d build` – **publishes** the `build/` folder to GitHub Pages |\n| `clean-files` | Removes `template/public` and `template/src` (used before copying updated template source) |\n| `copy-files` | Copies `src/` → `template/src` and `public/` → `template/public` |\n| `prepublishOnly` | Runs `clean-files` then `copy-files` – **prepares the template for npm publishing** |\n\n### 2. Scripts in `template.json` (delivered to projects created from this template)\n\nThese are the scripts a user gets after running `npx create-react-app my-app --template firebase-starter`:\n\n| Script | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `serve` | `serve -s build` – serves the production build locally (requires `serve` installed globally) |\n| `build-and-serve` | `npm run build && npm run serve` – **builds then serves the production build locally** |\n| `pull` | `git pull && npm i && npm start` – pulls latest code, installs deps, starts dev server |\n\n---\n\n## Repository Guidance for Testing a Production Build Locally Before Publishing\n\nThe **README** (under *\"To Deploy on GitHub Pages\"*, step 3) gives the following optional workflow:\n\n1. **Install `serve` globally** (if not already installed):\n   ```bash\n   npm i -g serve\n   ```\n\n2. **Temporarily set the `homepage` field** in `package.json` to `\"/\"` (so asset paths resolve correctly for local serving).\n\n3. **Run the combined build-and-serve command:**\n   ```bash\n   npm run build-and-serve\n   ```\n\nThis builds the production-optimised static site and immediately serves it locally so you can verify it works correctly **before** deploying to GitHub Pages with `npm run deploy`.\n\n> ⚠️ **Important note:** The `build-and-serve` script exists only in `template.json` – it is injected into projects *created from* the template. The template repository’s own `package.json` does **not** contain this script; it instead uses `prepublishOnly` to prepare the template for npm publishing.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1300, "prompt_tokens": 12202, "total_tokens": 13502, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 638, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 11648}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 11648, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 554}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "9395e45c-9418-4e05-9142-dfff9447abde", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea57d-5962-7e52-973e-a6b6f762a002-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12202, "output_tokens": 1300, "total_tokens": 13502, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 11648}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 638}}}}]}}}
